<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1773,1979]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
The presence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holloway" authorityYear="2009" box="[338,459,1773,1799]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ecpatia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis box="[338,459,1773,1799]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">E. obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[475,552,1773,1799]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1785,1810]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,184,1772]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,171,1774]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. 1a. Ecpatia grisescens sp. n., paratype male (Thailand, Lampang, Chae Hom, 07.x.2014.), wingspan 23 mm. 1b. E. grisescens sp. n., paratype female (Thailand, Lampang, Chae Hom, 26.vi.2015), wingspan 24 mm. 2a. E. spiculivalva sp. n., paratype male (Thailand, Lampang, Muban Phichai, 12.vi.2013), wingspan 24 mm. 2b. E. spiculivalva sp. n., paratype female (Thailand, Lampang, Muban Phichai, 23.v.2015), wingspan 24 mm. 3a. E. sciachroa male (Thailand, Lampang, Muban Phichai, 30.v.2009), wingspan 27 mm. 3b. E. sciachroa female (Thailand, Lampang, Muban Phichai, 29.vi.2011), wingspan 27 mm. 4. E. obscura male (Thailand, Lampang, Muban Phichai, 02.iii.2011), wingspan 26 mm. 5. E. longinquua male (Japan, Kagoshima pref. Amamioshima Is. 08.vi.2010, Teruhiko Fukuda leg.)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3227924/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Figs. 4</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[607,636,1773,1799]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–13" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1902,1927]" captionTargetBox="[314,1275,197,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[313,1275,174,1891]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 10–13. 10a. Male genitalia of E. sciachroa slide MJP111 (Thailand, Lampang, Muban Phichai, 30.v.2009), 10b. aedeagus slide MJP111. 11. Female genitalia, slide MJP112 (Thailand,27.ix.2009). 12a Male genitalia of E. obscura slide MJP1021 (Thailand, Lampang, Muban Phichai, 02.iii.2011). 12b aedeagus slide MJP1021. 13a Male genitalia of E. longinquua 13b aedeagus, slide of Teruhiko Fukuda Japan, Kagoshima pref. Amamioshima Is. 22.ii.2009." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3227928/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">12</figureCitation>
) Holloway in 
<collectingCountry box="[798,898,1773,1799]" name="Thailand" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Thailand</collectingCountry>
is confirmed, from northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1224,1328,1773,1799]" name="Thailand" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Thailand</collectingCountry>
: province 
<collectingRegion box="[151,262,1809,1835]" country="Thailand" name="Lampang" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Lampang</collectingRegion>
). It was identified by comparing its genitalia (slide no MJP1021) to fig.82. in Moths of Borneo, Part 13. One specimen was detected from 
<collectingCountry box="[529,633,1845,1871]" name="Thailand" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Thailand</collectingCountry>
: province 
<collectingRegion box="[748,857,1845,1871]" country="Thailand" name="Lampang" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Lampang</collectingRegion>
, Muban Phichai, 
<date box="[1052,1175,1845,1871]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" value="2011-03-02">02.iii.2011</date>
. Externally, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holloway" authorityYear="2009" box="[1315,1436,1845,1871]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ecpatia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis box="[1315,1436,1845,1871]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">E. obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closest to 
<taxonomicName box="[289,448,1881,1907]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ecpatia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longinquua">
<emphasis box="[289,448,1881,1907]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">E. longinquua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[462,524,1880,1907]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1785,1810]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,184,1772]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,171,1774]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. 1a. Ecpatia grisescens sp. n., paratype male (Thailand, Lampang, Chae Hom, 07.x.2014.), wingspan 23 mm. 1b. E. grisescens sp. n., paratype female (Thailand, Lampang, Chae Hom, 26.vi.2015), wingspan 24 mm. 2a. E. spiculivalva sp. n., paratype male (Thailand, Lampang, Muban Phichai, 12.vi.2013), wingspan 24 mm. 2b. E. spiculivalva sp. n., paratype female (Thailand, Lampang, Muban Phichai, 23.v.2015), wingspan 24 mm. 3a. E. sciachroa male (Thailand, Lampang, Muban Phichai, 30.v.2009), wingspan 27 mm. 3b. E. sciachroa female (Thailand, Lampang, Muban Phichai, 29.vi.2011), wingspan 27 mm. 4. E. obscura male (Thailand, Lampang, Muban Phichai, 02.iii.2011), wingspan 26 mm. 5. E. longinquua male (Japan, Kagoshima pref. Amamioshima Is. 08.vi.2010, Teruhiko Fukuda leg.)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3227924/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Fig 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1773,1979]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,500,1916,1943]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Genetic characterization.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holloway" authorityYear="2009" box="[507,627,1917,1943]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ecpatia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis box="[507,627,1917,1943]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">E. obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows a highly characteristic DNA barcode, the closest sequences available to us in BOLD are those of 
<taxonomicName box="[515,667,1953,1979]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ecpatia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dulcistriga">
<emphasis box="[515,667,1953,1979]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">E. dulcistriga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(7.52%).
</paragraph>
